<section id="our-story">
  <h2>Our Story 💫</h2>
  <p>We met in the university. We were both 17. I was in second year and you were a fresher.
  We met because we were supposed to start a Bacenta on campus together.
  I mean… we started the Bacenta 😅 — but as we kept the fellowship going, our hearts grew fonder 🥹❤️.</p>
  <p>Before we knew it, I enjoyed spending more time with you than even my books 😭.
  Unreasonable but magical 💕.</p>
  <p>It wasn’t love at first sight, but I love how long it took for you to start telling me
  “I haven’t heard from you the whole day.”
  Every day for four years, I thought about you, I came to your room, I ate your food,
  I tried to make you laugh 😅 — and I laughed at you even more —
  only to realize that I had melted to the ground;
  fallen so much in love no one could pick me up.</p>
  <p>On the 5th of July, 2022, I popped the question (not the biggest one but the phrase still works 😂😂).
  Fast forward… it’s been three years and I still really like you.
  I imagine what “happily ever after” with you looks like — teaching our 18-year-old how to drive,
  or celebrating “Kwaku and Lorrie’s 50th anniversary.”
  And I know there’s only one person I see all of that with: <strong>YOU</strong>.</p>
  <p>One fun memory? Oh I’ll never forget —
  Hillview Hotel.
  We knew outside food wasn’t allowed, but you and I strolled in with our Waakye 😂
  and found a way to eat it in plain sight.
  I was panicking the whole time that we’d get caught,
  yet somehow I was the one encouraging you to feel free and eat 😂😂😂.
  The only smart move? Buying Coke and lime from them —
  just to give off “we’re customers ooo” energy 😂</p>
  <p>And finally… I’ll forever laugh at your English —
  even though, technically, you understand and know way more words than I do 😭😂😂</p>
</section>

