<section id="future">
  <h2>🛤️ Where We’re Going… Together</h2>
  <p>I picture a life with you that spans across oceans and islands.
  Tropical skies above us, your laughter in my ears, and a camera roll full of sunsets and silly poses.
  From <strong>Zanzibar to Jamaica</strong>, <strong>Santorini to Switzerland</strong>, I want to see the world with you — because you are my world.</p>
  <p>I see a marriage full of joy — not because life will always be easy, but because <strong>I chose you</strong>.
  And if you were a twin, I’d still pick you.</p>
  <p>I see a home where <strong>you are our spiritual covering</strong>, where our children grow up learning to love God because they see it in you first.
  A home where I am cheered on, loved hard, and prayed for by my <strong>biggest support</strong> — you.</p>
  <p>And yes, I see our <strong>twins</strong> — <strong>Nyameye and Adom</strong> — running through the halls, laughing, learning, and being raised by two people madly in love.</p>
  <p><strong>Forever is real to me. Because it looks like you.</strong></p>
</section>

